## Next.js 16 / React 19 conventions

- **Server Components first.** `'use client'` lives on the leaves; never on a layout or page when a leaf could carry it.
- **Async dynamic APIs (Next 15+).** `cookies()`, `headers()`, `params`, `searchParams` are all async — always `await` them. Sync access is a runtime error.
- **Server Actions.** Mark with `'use server'` at the top of the file or function. Validate inputs server-side with zod even when the client already validated.
- **Cache busting.** Use `revalidatePath('/route')` or `revalidateTag('tag')` from a mutation server action. Do NOT use `force-dynamic` to "fix" stale data — find the real cause.
- **Parallel data fetches.** Use `Promise.all` for independent reads inside a Server Component to avoid waterfalls.
- **Route-level loading.** Ship `loading.tsx` next to every meaningful route segment; wrap below-fold content in `<Suspense>` with a sensible fallback.
- **Lazy heavy components.** Charts, editors, maps, PDF, 3D, rich-text — load via `lazyClient` from `@/lib/lazy` (or `next/dynamic` for one-offs). Keep `'use client'` boundaries minimal.
- **Images.** `next/image` with explicit `width`/`height`. `priority` ONLY on the LCP hero image. Decorative images get `alt=""`.
- **Links.** `<Link prefetch>` is the default; only opt out for huge below-fold routes.
- **Navigation snappiness.** `await` only critical work pre-navigate. Fire-and-forget non-critical work via `void` + `startTransition(() => router.push(...))` / `useTransitionRouter()`.

## Don'ts

- Don't `'use client'` on layouts or pages.
- Don't sync-read `cookies()`/`headers()` (Next 15+ breaks this).
- Don't add barrel `index.ts` re-exports (hurts tree-shake + cycles).
- Don't use parallel/intercepting routes unless the UX truly requires them.
- Don't call `router.refresh()` in event handlers without measuring — prefer `revalidatePath`/`revalidateTag` from a server action.

See `.agents/rules/performance.md` and `.agents/rules/lazy-loading.md` for the full sheet.
